               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem class="#monastica" n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_618-item1">
                     <locus>(fol. 2)</locus>
                     <author key="person_3343"><supplied>Ps.-Adalgerus (Ps.-Isidore)</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_6368"><supplied>Commonitiuncula ad sororem</supplied></title>
                     <note>(<ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=CPL&amp;number=1219"><title>CPL</title> 1219</ref>)</note>
                     <finalRubric>Ammonicio</finalRubric>
                     <note>The first leaf is lost, but a list of contents is on fol. 1. It is a religious treatise of advice (admonitio) to a nun, in 15 chapters: the first is De laude Caritatis, the second De Humilitatis virtute (beg. 'Certissime uero tibi conuenit').</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_618-item2">
                     <locus>(fol. 43)</locus>
                     <author key="person_104113324">Ps.-Albertus Magnus</author>
                     <title key="work_3823">Paradisus animae</title>
                     <rubric>Alberti magni doctoris laudatissimi de uirtutibus anime ueris &amp; perfectis, quas gratuitas uocat</rubric>
                     <incipit type="prol.">Sicut quedam uicia</incipit>
                     <note>A leaf is lost after fol. 44. Four verses on the treatise, and a list of chapters precede.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_618-item2a">
                     <note> A few later theological and other notes, including a praise of Printing (by John Davies, 1590: see <bibl>C. Davies, <title>John Davies of Malwydd</title> (2004), p. 116</bibl>), are on fols. iii, iv, v, 140.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
